The
hall

shade.
Lulu

still

The
fire

the
chair

ottoman

gone
too.
Down

left
is
a
small
tea-table,
with
a
coffee-pot
and
a
cup
of

black
coffee
on
it,
and
an
arm-chair
next
it.

In
this
chair,
deep
in
cushions,
with
a
plaid
shawl
over

her
knees,
sits
Countess
Geschwit
in
a
tight
black
dress.

Rodrigo,
clad
as
a
servant,
sits
on
the
ottoman.
At
the

rear,
Alva
Schon
is
walking
up
and
down
before
the

entrance
door.

RODRIGO.
He
lets
people
wait
for
him
as
if
he
were

a
concert
conductor!

GESCHWITZ.
I
beg
of
you,
don't
speak!

my

a
head

piness
